    <briefdescription>
<para>Neutral node-status contract for every <ref refid="namespaceOpenSkyhawk" kindref="compound">OpenSkyhawk</ref> node (<ref refid="namespacePanelGroup" kindref="compound">PanelGroup</ref>, <ref refid="namespacePanelBridge" kindref="compound">PanelBridge</ref>, PDU). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Owns the cross-node <bold>status API</bold> — not just health:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>the <computeroutput>_NODE_STATUS</computeroutput> DCS-BIOS host-reporting contract (proto version, request address, message names) — <bold>the canonical source the client&apos;s <computeroutput>sync-a4ec.ts</computeroutput> parses</bold>;</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>NodeHealthFlag</computeroutput> (HEALTH_n flag bits) and <computeroutput>NodeFaultCode</computeroutput> (the compact wire faultId dictionary the client maps to labels);</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>FaultSource</computeroutput> — the interface a fault-producing object implements so a node-level aggregator can roll it up. A <computeroutput>FaultSource</computeroutput> is <emphasis>one piece</emphasis> of node status, not the whole story.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>This is the neutral home for node-status vocabulary so it isn&apos;t shaped around any one node flavour (PanelGroup/OutputBase) or the HID namespace. <computeroutput>NodeHealthPayload</computeroutput> (the CAN HEALTH_n frame struct) stays in <computeroutput><ref refid="CANProtocol_8h" kindref="compound">CANProtocol.h</ref></computeroutput>; the fault <emphasis>detail</emphasis> strings stay local (DiagSerial), never on the wire. Header-only contract + a tiny <computeroutput>FaultSource</computeroutput> registry (<computeroutput><ref refid="NodeStatus_8cpp" kindref="compound">NodeStatus.cpp</ref></computeroutput>).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="version"><para>0.1.0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="copyright"><para>GPL-2.0-only — see Firmware/LICENSE </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
